## How to Add Screenshots

1. Take screenshots of your application
2. Save them in this directory with the following names:
   - `screenshot.png` - Main preview (recommended: 1200x630px)
   - `welcome.png` - Welcome screen
   - `quiz.png` - Quiz in action
   - `results.png` - Results screen

3. The main README.md will automatically display `screenshot.png`

## Recommended Dimensions

- **Main Screenshot**: 1200x630px (GitHub social preview)
- **Other Screenshots**: 1920x1080px or 1280x720px

## Tips for Great Screenshots

- Use actual quiz data (not Lorem Ipsum)
- Include browser chrome for context
- Show key features in action
- Use light backgrounds for better visibility
- Crop unnecessary whitespace

## Alternative: Use Placeholder

Until you add your own screenshot, the README will show a link.
You can use services like:
- https://placeholder.com/
- https://via.placeholder.com/
- Or create a simple banner with Canva/Figma
